{# Full feature-by-feature comparison of the four public tiers.
   No props — all values are static and match docs/05-monetization.md.
   The "AI Insights" row is conditional on the `ai_available` Twig global.

   TASK-118: the "Reports / month" row carries a "What counts? →" footnote
   link anchored to `#faq-what-counts-as-report` in PricingFaq below.
   TASK-124: the three feature rows whose meaning isn't self-evident from
   the label alone (Sender inventory, Blacklist monitoring, White-label
   PDF reports) carry a daisyUI `tooltip` ⓘ icon that hovers a one-line
   definition AND deep-links to the matching glossary FAQ entry. Both
   the desktop matrix and the mobile cards get the same treatment so
   the buyer experience is parity.

   The tooltip markup is inlined (rather than a macro call) because this
   template renders as a `<twig:>` component, where `_self` macro
   resolution is brittle across UX-component / TwigPreLexer revisions —
   inline is the boring, durable choice. #}

{% set check %}
<svg class="w-4 h-4 text-success inline" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.5 12.75l6 6 9-13.5"/>
</svg>
{% endset %}

{% set dash %}<span class="text-base-content/30">—</span>{% endset %}

{# Reusable info-pill markup — captured into a variable so each row stays
   readable. The wrapping <span class="tooltip"> is daisyUI's tooltip
   primitive; `data-tip` carries the short label. The inner <a> targets
   the glossary FAQ entry so keyboard / screen-reader users can follow
   through to the full definition. #}
{% set senderInventoryTip %}
<span class="tooltip tooltip-right align-middle ml-1" data-tip="Every IP / SMTP host that sends mail as you, with authorize-or-revoke decisions per sender.">
    <a href="#faq-sender-inventory" class="text-base-content/40 hover:text-primary" aria-label="What is the sender inventory? Learn more">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 inline" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M11.25 11.25l.041-.02a.75.75 0 011.063.852l-.708 2.836a.75.75 0 001.063.853l.041-.021M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0zm-9-3.75h.008v.008H12V8.25z"/>
        </svg>
    </a>
</span>
{% endset %}

{% set blacklistTip %}
<span class="tooltip tooltip-right align-middle ml-1" data-tip="Continuous DNS-based RBL checks (Spamhaus, Barracuda…) on every sending IP, with alerts when one gets listed.">
    <a href="#faq-blacklist-monitoring" class="text-base-content/40 hover:text-primary" aria-label="What is blacklist monitoring? Learn more">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 inline" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M11.25 11.25l.041-.02a.75.75 0 011.063.852l-.708 2.836a.75.75 0 001.063.853l.041-.021M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0zm-9-3.75h.008v.008H12V8.25z"/>
        </svg>
    </a>
</span>
{% endset %}

{% set whiteLabelTip %}
<span class="tooltip tooltip-right align-middle ml-1" data-tip="Monthly aggregate report exports with your company branding (logo, colors, footer) — not Sendvery's.">
    <a href="#faq-white-label-pdf" class="text-base-content/40 hover:text-primary" aria-label="What is white-label PDF? Learn more">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 inline" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M11.25 11.25l.041-.02a.75.75 0 011.063.852l-.708 2.836a.75.75 0 001.063.853l.041-.021M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0zm-9-3.75h.008v.008H12V8.25z"/>
        </svg>
    </a>
</span>
{% endset %}

